WEBVTT

00:03.930 --> 00:05.761
[ SCOFFS ]

00:05.800 --> 00:08.598
ALL THOSE TIMES I BROUGHT HIM
COFFEE WITHOUT HIM EVEN ASKING.

00:08.640 --> 00:09.902
WHO?

00:09.940 --> 00:11.669
OLIVER.
WHAT DO YOU MEAN, WHO?

00:11.710 --> 00:14.270
LOOK, IT'S MORE
THAN A BOSS THING.

00:14.310 --> 00:15.470
OKAY?
I TRUSTED HIM.

00:15.510 --> 00:18.399
I WOULD EVEN GO SO FAR
AS TO SAY I LOVED HIM.

00:18.450 --> 00:21.772
AND WHAT DOES HE DO?
HE JUST STABBED ME IN THE BACK.

00:21.820 --> 00:23.378
BACKSTABBING IS NOT
REALLY OLIVER'S THING.

00:23.420 --> 00:26.082
I MEAN, ALL THAT THOUGHT THAT I
PUT INTO HIS SECRET SANTA GIFI'.

00:26.120 --> 00:27.781
DO YOU EVEN UNDERSTAND
HOW HARD IT IS

00:27.820 --> 00:31.449
TO FIND SOMETHING CREATIVE AND
-- AND -- AND THOUGHTFUL...

00:31.490 --> 00:33.993
[ SIGHS ]
...FOR UNDER $30?

00:34.030 --> 00:36.260
I THINK MAYBE YOU'RE GOOD
ON THE COFFEE FRONT.

00:38.330 --> 00:39.797
I'M GENUINELY MAD
RIGHT NOW.

00:39.840 --> 00:41.990
WELL,
WHY DON'T YOU TALK TO HIM?

00:42.040 --> 00:43.803
MNH-MNH.
NO?

00:43.840 --> 00:45.637
NO, I'M GONNA PRETEND
EVERYTHING'S FINE.

00:45.670 --> 00:47.774
OKAY, THAT'S --
THAT'LL WORK.
IT WILL WORK,

00:47.810 --> 00:49.277
BECAUSE I'M JUST GONNA
PUT A SMILE ON MY FACE

00:49.310 --> 00:50.242
UNTIL I'M ACTUALLY HAPPY.

00:50.280 --> 00:51.975
BUT YOU'RE NOT KNOWN
FOR YOUR POKER FACE.

00:52.010 --> 00:54.444
REALLY?
MM-HMM.

00:54.480 --> 00:56.289
WHAT AM I THINKING
RIGHT NOW?

00:56.320 --> 00:57.617
PROBABLY THAT IF I DON'T
TELL YOU YOU LOOK HAPPY,

00:57.650 --> 00:58.639
YOU'LL KILL ME IN MY SLEEP.

00:58.690 --> 01:00.419
HA! THAT IS WHAT
I WANTED YOU TO THINK.

01:00.460 --> 01:02.826
I WAS ACTUALLY THINKING
SOMETHING COMPLETELY DIFFERENT.

01:02.860 --> 01:05.021
OKAY, DEAR, WHATEVER GETS YOU
THROUGH THE NIGHT.

01:05.060 --> 01:07.449
YOU GET ME
THROUGH THE NIGHT.

01:09.100 --> 01:10.499
WHAT I NEED IS SOMETHING
TO GET ME THROUGH THE DAY.

01:10.530 --> 01:13.260
REALLY?

01:21.280 --> 01:24.670
I'M STILL MAD.

01:24.710 --> 01:27.838
I'D LIKE TO OPEN UP THINGS
TO THE ROOM.

01:27.880 --> 01:30.781
IS THERE ANYBODY WITH US
HERE TODAY

01:30.820 --> 01:33.482
THAT IS HERE
FOR THE FIRST TIME?

01:33.520 --> 01:38.878
UM...DAVE...YOU MENTIONED
ON YOUR WAY IN

01:38.930 --> 01:40.898
THAT THIS WAS
YOUR FIRST MEETING.

01:40.930 --> 01:43.797
IT IS DAVE, RIGHT?

01:43.830 --> 01:47.334
YEAH, UH,
MY NAME'S DAVE.

01:47.370 --> 01:49.861
All: HI, DAVE.

01:49.910 --> 01:51.639
[ SIGHS ]
[ SLURPS ]

01:51.670 --> 01:53.206
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

01:53.240 --> 01:55.936
NOT REALLY SURE WHAT TO SAY.

01:55.980 --> 01:59.245
I'M NOT THAT GOOD
AT...SHARING.

01:59.280 --> 02:00.713
[ CHUCKLES ]

02:00.750 --> 02:02.809
YOU KNOW,
UNLESS YOU'VE HAD A FEW.

02:02.850 --> 02:04.249
[ Chuckling ] RIGHT?

02:04.290 --> 02:07.680
UM, I GUESS I'M HERE BECAUSE
MY ROOMMATE SUGGESTED IT.

02:07.720 --> 02:11.258
HE THOUGHT IT MIGHT SLOW THINGS
DOWN A LITTLE...

02:14.060 --> 02:16.528
GOT A PRETTY STRESSFUL JOB,

02:16.570 --> 02:22.133
AND I LOST CUSTODY OF MY...SON

02:22.170 --> 02:25.139
[SIGHS] WHO TURNED OUT
TO ACTUALLY NOT BE MY SON.

02:25.170 --> 02:28.799
IT'S NOT THAT
I'M AN ADDICT PER SE.

02:28.840 --> 02:33.072
IT'S JUST THAT I'M JUST FEELING
A LITTLE LOST.

02:33.120 --> 02:38.342
SO...YEAH... THAT'S --
THAT'S IT. THAT'S IT.

02:39.520 --> 02:41.249
Together: THANKS, DAVE.

02:41.290 --> 02:43.053
THAN KS.

02:43.090 --> 02:44.887
HEY, MAN.
THANKS FOR WAITING.

02:44.930 --> 02:46.420
NO PROBLEM.
HOW WAS IT?

02:46.460 --> 02:47.620
IT WAS GREAT.

02:47.660 --> 02:49.469
SERIOUSLY?
YEAH.

02:49.500 --> 02:52.264
I MEAN, I KNOW I DIDN'T WANT
TO GO AT FIRST,

02:52.300 --> 02:55.235
BUT NOW THAT I DID,
I THINK IT WAS A GOOD IDEA.

02:55.270 --> 02:57.363
UH, IT'S NICE
JUST TO TALK.

02:57.410 --> 03:00.072
YOU KNOW, I FEEL LIGHTER.

03:00.110 --> 03:02.578
SERIOUSLY.
IT WAS AWESOME.

03:02.610 --> 03:04.339
*A,B,C,D

03:04.380 --> 03:05.972
* BOOGIE DOWN

03:06.010 --> 03:10.982
[ SIREN WAILS ]

03:11.020 --> 03:14.148
"SUPERSEDE" -- C-E-D-E?

03:14.190 --> 03:16.454
S-E-D-E.

03:16.490 --> 03:19.527
IT'S LATIN FOR "SEAT."

03:19.560 --> 03:23.326
I WATCH A LOT OF "JEOPARDY!"
WHEN I CAN'T SLEEP.

03:23.370 --> 03:26.760
HOW'S THE WARRANT COMING?

03:26.800 --> 03:29.405
WELL, IT'D BE GOING A LOT FASTER
IF THE SPELLCHECK WAS WORKING.

03:29.440 --> 03:30.600
WELL, I NEED IT AS SOON

03:30.640 --> 03:32.335
AS OLIVER GIVES ME
A TEAM OF UNIFORMS. YEAH.

03:32.380 --> 03:33.472
DETECTIVE, IF POSSIBLE,

03:33.510 --> 03:35.034
I'D LIKE TO BE A PART
OF THIS RAID YOU'RE DOING.

03:35.080 --> 03:37.071
WHY DO YOU THINK I'M LETTING YOU
WRITE THE WARRANT?

03:37.110 --> 03:38.543
YOU'RE GONNA LEAD THE TEAM
FROM 15.

03:38.580 --> 03:39.444
YOU CANNOT BE SERIOUS.

03:39.480 --> 03:41.539
WHAT?
I'VE DONE ENTRIES.

03:41.580 --> 03:43.787
I'M GOOD AT TACTICAL.

03:43.820 --> 03:45.048
OH.

03:45.090 --> 03:46.682
WHAT IS THAT?

03:46.720 --> 03:48.415
IT'S FROM DEX'S LAWYER.

03:48.460 --> 03:50.348
YEAH?

03:50.390 --> 03:52.392
HE'S GOING
FOR FULL SPOUSAL SUPPORT,

03:52.430 --> 03:53.454
CHILD SUPPORT,

03:53.500 --> 03:55.821
AND HE WANTS LEO
FIVE NIGHTS A WEEK.

03:55.860 --> 03:56.861
NO, NO, NO.

03:56.900 --> 03:58.367
NO, THERE'S NO WAY
HE CAN ASK THAT.

03:58.400 --> 03:59.958
WELL, HE'S GOT THE BEST FAMILY
LAWYER IN THE CITY REPPING HIM,

04:00.000 --> 04:02.503
WHICH I DON'T EVEN KNOW
HOW HE CAN AFFORD HER.

04:02.540 --> 04:05.304
IF I DON'T AGREE TO THIS,
THEY'RE TAKING ME TO COURT.

04:05.340 --> 04:07.331
[ SIGHS ]

04:07.380 --> 04:08.608
HE'S GOING
FOR SOLE CUSTODY.

04:08.640 --> 04:11.200
T-T-THEY'RE JUST
TRYING TO SCARE YOU.

04:11.250 --> 04:12.547
[ Chuckling ]
IT'S WORKING.

04:12.580 --> 04:14.241
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

04:14.280 --> 04:15.577
GOOD MORNING, JOHN.

04:15.620 --> 04:17.212
IN DETECTIVE PECK'S RAID,

04:17.250 --> 04:19.855
I SEE YOU'VE ALLOCATED UNITS
TO ASSIST.

04:19.890 --> 04:21.517
I HAVE.

04:21.560 --> 04:23.653
UNDERGROUND GAMBLING OPERATION,
FUNDING GANG ACTIVITY.

04:23.690 --> 04:25.851
THAT'S PETTY CRIMINALS
PLAYING POKER IN A DIVE BAR.

04:25.890 --> 04:27.858
IN OUR OWN BACKYARD.

04:27.900 --> 04:29.492
YEAH, WE SHUT IT DOWN, ANOTHER
ONE POPS UP A BLOCK AWAY.

04:29.530 --> 04:31.361
IT'S A WASTE OF RESOURCES.

04:31.400 --> 04:32.867
INSPECTOR?

04:32.900 --> 04:35.039
I'D LIKE YOU TO DOUBLE UP
PATROLS IN SWANSEA FOR THE WEEK.

04:35.070 --> 04:37.038
I DON'T HAVE THE UNIFORMS
FOR BOTH.

04:37.070 --> 04:38.332
THIS SWANSEA ISSUE
IS A DELICATE ONE,

04:38.370 --> 04:39.871
AND IT'S IMPORTANT TO ME.

04:39.910 --> 04:41.400
IT'S A MIDDLE-CLASS
NEIGHBORHOOD

04:41.440 --> 04:43.749
WITH A CRIME RATE
THAT'S BELOW --
IS THAT A "NO"?

04:43.780 --> 04:46.248
IF I PULL THE PLUG
ON THIS RAID,

04:46.280 --> 04:48.669
I-I GOT TO GIVE PECK
A REASON.

04:48.720 --> 04:50.039
AND I'M SURE
YOU'LL COME UP WITH ONE.

04:50.090 --> 04:51.409
THANK YOU, STAFF.

04:51.450 --> 04:54.180
TRULY APPRECIATE
YOUR COOPERATION.

04:57.660 --> 05:01.721
SCREW YOU, WEDNESDAY.

05:01.760 --> 05:03.728
HEY, GOOD MORNING, SIR.

05:03.770 --> 05:05.590
HEY, I JUST WANTED TO GIVE YOU
A HEADS-UP

05:05.630 --> 05:06.665
THAT DETECTIVE PECK ASKED

05:06.700 --> 05:07.997
THAT I BE A POINT MAN
ON THE RAID TEAM.

05:08.040 --> 05:09.598
FORGET ABOUT THAT RAID.
IT'S NOT HAPPENING -- NOT TODAY.

05:09.640 --> 05:11.062
SIT DOWN.

05:11.110 --> 05:12.429
WELCOME TO WEDNESDAY!

05:12.480 --> 05:15.438
TODAY OUR FOCUS
IS ON COMMUNITY POLICING,

05:15.480 --> 05:17.141
VISIBILITY, AND OPTICS.

05:17.180 --> 05:18.249
HOLD ON TO YOUR HATS, FOLKS.

05:18.280 --> 05:19.975
TODAY WE'RE DOUBLING OUR PATROLS
IN SWANSEA.

05:20.020 --> 05:20.873
OOH, EMERGENCY.

05:20.920 --> 05:22.148
BUST A BUNCH OF HIPSTERS

05:22.180 --> 05:24.284
DRINKING BLUE RIBBON
IN HIGH PARK. OOH.

05:24.320 --> 05:26.686
MCNALLY, YOU CAN BE LATE
OR YOU CAN BE MOUTHY.

05:26.720 --> 05:27.584
YOU CHOOSE ONE.

05:27.620 --> 05:29.986
SO...

05:30.030 --> 05:31.657
NOW THAT I'M PUBLICLY
SHAMING YOU,

05:31.690 --> 05:33.749
EPSTEIN, THANK YOU. YOU BLEW OFF
THE BREAKFAST MEETING

05:33.800 --> 05:35.529
THAT I SET UP FOR YOU
WITH SERGEANT ROLLINS

05:35.560 --> 05:36.595
IN THE INTELLIGENCE UNIT.

05:36.630 --> 05:38.962
I'M SORRY, SIR.
I-I-I COMPLETELY FORGOT.

05:39.000 --> 05:40.831
WELL,
SO MUCH FOR INTELLIGENCE.

05:40.870 --> 05:42.132
BUT, DIAZ, YOU'RE HERE.

05:42.170 --> 05:44.604
I'M SO HAPPY YOU BOTHERED
TO SHOW UP AT ALL.

05:44.640 --> 05:47.438
I'VE BEEN LETTING THIS SLIDE,
ALL OF IT, FOR WAY TOO LONG.

05:47.480 --> 05:49.641
I'VE BEEN YOUR SOUNDING BOARD,
YOUR FRIEND.

05:49.680 --> 05:51.477
WHAT DOES IT GET ME?
MORE PROBLEMS.

05:51.510 --> 05:53.239
WHAT YOU DO
ISN'T JUST ABOUT YOU.

05:53.280 --> 05:56.044
IT AFFECT S ALL OF US.
GET IT TOGETHER.

05:56.080 --> 05:57.945
ASSIGNMENTS ARE ON THE BOARD.
DISMISSED.

06:02.860 --> 06:04.680
I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHERE OLIVER WENT.

06:04.730 --> 06:06.322
IT'S LIKE
HE'S BEEN DELETED --

06:06.360 --> 06:08.453
YOU KNOW, REPLACED
BY A COMPANY ROBOT MAN.

06:08.500 --> 06:11.628
[ LAUGHING ]

06:11.670 --> 06:13.297
WHAT?

06:13.340 --> 06:16.400
YOU SAID SOMETHING BAD
ABOUT ANOTHER PERSON.

06:16.440 --> 06:18.203
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

06:18.240 --> 06:21.073
WE FINALLY HAVE SOMETHING
IN COMMON, MCNALLY.

06:21.110 --> 06:24.045
OH, NO,
WE'LL ALWAYS HAVE NICK.

06:24.080 --> 06:25.968
MM.

06:26.010 --> 06:27.477
WE BOTH KNOW THIS DETAIL'S
A JOKE.

06:27.520 --> 06:28.612
WHAT HAS HAPPENED TO YOU?

06:28.650 --> 06:30.686
HEY, DID YOU LOSE YOUR
MAGICAL GIRL GUIDE SASH?

06:30.720 --> 06:33.382
YOU KNOW, THE ONE THAT BESTOWS
ALL YOUR EXTRA-NICE SUPERPOWERS?

06:33.420 --> 06:35.012
THAT IS FUNNY.
YOU LOVED THAT SASH.

06:35.060 --> 06:37.153
THAT'S FUNNY.
THAT'S REALLY FUNNY.

06:37.190 --> 06:38.521
ALL I'M SAYING IS

06:38.560 --> 06:40.790
THAT THIS SHIFT IS GONNA BE FULL
OF THE STUPIDEST CALLS --

06:40.830 --> 06:43.993
NOISE COMPLAINTS
AND STOLEN GARDEN GNOMES.

06:44.030 --> 06:47.295
Woman: 1519, WE'VE GOT AN
ANIMAL COMPLAINT IN YOUR ZONE.

06:47.340 --> 06:50.434
A MAN REPORTS HIS HOSTILE CAT
HAS TRAPPED HIM IN HIS CLOSET.

06:50.470 --> 06:51.937
SEE?! HOW?! SEE?!

06:51.970 --> 06:54.973
OKAY, THEN LET SOMEBODY ELSE
TAKE ENE CALL.

06:56.910 --> 06:59.447
YOU'RE GONNA DODGE A CALL?
REALLY?

06:59.480 --> 07:03.439
1519, ARE YOU 10-8?

07:08.920 --> 07:12.253
OKAY. UH, 1519.
WE'RE ON OUR WAY.

07:12.290 --> 07:14.554
SHUT UP.

07:14.600 --> 07:16.090
HEY.

07:16.130 --> 07:19.361
HEY.
SORRY ABOUT THE RAID.

07:19.400 --> 07:20.799
DID OLIVER SAY
WHY HE'S CALLING IT OFF?

07:20.840 --> 07:24.230
OH, POLITICAL SITUATION,
MANPOWER ALLOCATION,

07:24.270 --> 07:26.067
A FEW OTHER BUZZWORDS,
YOU KNOW, BUT IT'S FINE.

07:26.110 --> 07:29.273
THESE GUYS PLAY EVERY WEDNESDAY,
SO -- WHICH IS WHY I'M HERE.

07:29.310 --> 07:31.141
CAN I TALK TO YOU
FOR A SECOND?

07:35.380 --> 07:36.745
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

07:36.790 --> 07:39.042
OKAY, THIS CAN'T GO FURTHER
THAN US.

07:39.090 --> 07:41.012
[ BREATH ES DEEPLY ]

07:41.060 --> 07:43.381
I KNOW WHERE DEX IS GETTING
HIS MONEY FOR HIS LAWYER.

07:43.430 --> 07:46.456
WE CAUGHT HIM ON SURVEILLANCE
AT THE GAMBLING CLUB.

07:46.500 --> 07:47.592
HE'S A REGULAR.

07:47.630 --> 07:49.029
DEX ISN'T IN A GANG.

07:49.060 --> 07:52.063
NO, HE'S AT THEIR POKER GAME
EVERY WEDNESDAY.

07:52.100 --> 07:55.592
HE SAID HE HAD THERAPY
ON WEDNESDAYS.
[ SCOFFS ]

07:55.640 --> 07:57.665
YOU KNOW, OKAY,
WHEN WE DO THIS RAID,

07:57.710 --> 07:58.938
IF HE'S IN THERE,

07:58.970 --> 08:01.677
HE'LL BE CHARGED WITH BEING
IN AN ILLEGAL GAMING HOUSE.

08:03.180 --> 08:05.273
HE CAN SERVE
UP TO TWO YEARS.

08:05.310 --> 08:06.618
YOU'RE GONNA ARREST HIM?

08:06.650 --> 08:08.777
TRACI, YOU'RE NOT RESPONSIBLE
FOR THIS GUY.

08:08.820 --> 08:10.845
YOU'RE RESPONSIBLE FOR LEO
AND YOURSELF.

08:10.890 --> 08:12.619
OKAY? THAT'S IT.

08:12.660 --> 08:14.616
AND AS SOON AS THIS RAID
HAPPENS -- OKAY? --

08:14.660 --> 08:15.786
WHICH IT WILL, EVENTUALLY,

08:15.820 --> 08:17.481
HE WON'T HAVE A CASE
AGAINST YOU.

08:17.530 --> 08:18.986
UNBELIEVABLE.

08:19.030 --> 08:21.123
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

08:21.160 --> 08:22.718
CHLOE KNOWS SOMETHING'S UP.

08:22.770 --> 08:24.988
SHE KEEPS ASKING ME
WHAT'S GOING ON.

08:25.030 --> 08:26.395
SHE KNOWS
I'VE BEEN AVOIDING HER.

08:26.430 --> 08:28.330
YOU CAN'T CONTROL WHAT COMES OUT
OF CHLOE'S MOUTH.

08:28.370 --> 08:30.008
OKAY, COULD YOU PLEASE
JUST NOT TELL HER?

08:30.040 --> 08:32.702
I WON'T.

08:32.740 --> 08:35.334
IF YOU CAN KEEP OUR STUFF
BETWEEN US, THAT'D BE GREAT.

08:35.380 --> 08:36.938
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

08:36.980 --> 08:38.538
SO, WHAT WAS OLIVER
TALKING ABOUT AT PARADE --

08:38.580 --> 08:39.740
YOU MISSED
SOME SORT OF MEETING?

08:39.780 --> 08:41.441
AW, YEAH, I WAS SUPPOSED
TO SIT DOWN

08:41.480 --> 08:43.016
WITH THIS GUY
FROM INTELLIGENCE,

08:43.050 --> 08:44.984
BUY HIM A COFFEE,
SEE WHAT THE JOB ENTAILS.

08:45.020 --> 08:47.409
BUT YOU MISSED IT 'CAUSE
YOU WERE CHAPERONING ME.

08:47.460 --> 08:48.916
WASN'T A BIG DEAL.

08:48.960 --> 08:50.427
LOOK, I'M GOOD, OKAY?

08:50.460 --> 08:52.792
WE'RE COOL.
I DON'T NEED A BABYSITTER.

08:52.830 --> 08:55.390
I KNOW.

08:55.430 --> 08:58.365
UNIT 1504, CALL RADIO.

08:58.400 --> 09:00.197
1504. GO.

09:00.240 --> 09:02.538
1504, ATTEND
4-9 LAKEPORT AVENUE.

09:02.570 --> 09:05.266
NEIGHBOR REPORTS
UNOCCUPIED VEHICLE IDLING

09:05.310 --> 09:06.334
FOR A PROLONGED
PERIOD OF TIME.

09:06.370 --> 09:07.439
COPY.

09:07.480 --> 09:08.833
PROLONGED PERIOD OF TIME?

09:08.880 --> 09:11.201
BETTER STEP ON IT.
PLANET NEEDS OUR HELP.

09:11.250 --> 09:13.070
LIVING THE DREAM.

09:18.020 --> 09:20.955
[ ENGINE SHUTS OFF ]

09:20.990 --> 09:22.787
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

09:28.300 --> 09:30.461
[ ENGINE IDLING ]

09:37.140 --> 09:38.562
[ ENGINE SHUTS OFF ]

09:38.610 --> 09:40.908
THE WHOLE THING
SMELLS LIKE COCONUTS.

09:40.940 --> 09:42.498
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

09:42.540 --> 09:44.849
I MEAN, THE CAR
SMELLS LIKE COCONUTS.

09:44.880 --> 09:47.747
GOT TO BE SUN BLOCK
OR SOMETHING.

09:47.780 --> 09:49.748
DOOR'S OPEN.

09:52.190 --> 09:54.750
HELLO! IS ANYONE HOME?!

09:54.790 --> 09:59.386
THIS IS THE POLICE.
WE'RE COMING INSIDE.

09:59.430 --> 10:02.399
Chris: WE GOT A COMPLAINT
ABOUT YOUR VEHICLE.

10:02.430 --> 10:04.694
IS ANYONE HOME?!

10:06.640 --> 10:10.508
DOV: THIS IS THE POLICE.
IS ANYONE HOME?

10:10.540 --> 10:12.838
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

10:15.310 --> 10:17.574
[ POUNDING ON DOOR]

10:17.610 --> 10:20.317
Man: HEY! I'M IN HERE!
I'M HERE!

10:20.350 --> 10:22.716
IN HERE! HELP ME!

10:22.750 --> 10:25.082
I'M IN HERE!
HEY!

10:25.120 --> 10:26.542
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]
OH, MY GOD.

10:26.590 --> 10:28.911
THEY LOCKED ME IN.

10:28.960 --> 10:30.655
WHO?

10:30.690 --> 10:32.385
WHOEVER WAS ROBBING
THE PLACE, MAN.

10:32.430 --> 10:34.523
I WALKED IN THE HOUSE.

10:34.560 --> 10:35.697
SOMEONE WAS HERE,
SO I RAN IN HERE.

10:35.730 --> 10:36.424
THEY SLAMMED THE DOOR.

10:36.460 --> 10:38.360
ARE YOU THE HOMEOWNER?

10:38.400 --> 10:39.560
YEAH.
YES. YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.

10:39.600 --> 10:41.090
I LIVE HERE WITH MY WIFE
AND MY SON --

10:41.140 --> 10:42.539
MY STEPSON.
[ THUD IN DISTANCE ]

10:42.570 --> 10:44.333
I'M GONNA GO CHECK THE REST
OF THE HOUSE.

10:44.370 --> 10:46.031
WHERE ARE THEY NOW?

10:46.070 --> 10:47.503
OH, MY --
MY SON'S AT SCHOOL.

10:47.540 --> 10:48.632
MY WIFE'S AT THE AIRPORT.

10:48.680 --> 10:50.409
WE -- WE WERE ON OUR WAY
OUT OF TOWN,

10:50.450 --> 10:52.145
AND H FORGOT
MY PASSPORT, RIGHT?

10:52.180 --> 10:53.169
SO I BOMBED BACK HERE,

10:53.220 --> 10:54.847
AND WHEN I PULLED IN
THE DRIVEWAY,

10:54.880 --> 10:56.211
THE FRONT DOOR WAS OPEN.

10:56.250 --> 10:58.218
IS THAT YOUR CAR OUT FRONT?
YEAH.

10:58.250 --> 11:00.309
SO I WALK IN, AND THE PLACE
IS, LIKE, TOTALLY RANSACKED.

11:00.360 --> 11:02.726
SO I RAN INTO THE STUDIO HERE
TO CHECK ON MY GEAR, AND --

11:02.760 --> 11:04.580
ALL RIGHT, YOU SAID
SOMEBODY LOCKED YOU IN.

11:04.630 --> 11:06.029
UH, YEAH,
THE DOOR'S BUSTED.

11:06.060 --> 11:07.755
IT'S BEEN BUSTED
SINCE WE MOVED IN.

11:07.800 --> 11:09.449
YOU CAN'T OPEN IT
FROM THE INSIDE.

11:11.000 --> 11:14.128
MAIN FLOOR IS CLEAR.
I'M HEADING UPSTAIRS.

11:14.170 --> 11:17.003
YEP. ALL RIGHT.
[ Sighing ] OH, GOD.

11:17.040 --> 11:18.462
LET'S JUST GO
FROM THE TOP.

11:18.510 --> 11:20.501
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]
CHRIS!

11:20.540 --> 11:21.677
GET UP HERE!

11:21.710 --> 11:23.302
DISPATCH, THIS IS 1504

11:23.350 --> 11:26.649
REQUESTING E.M.S. AND BACKUP
FOR A POSSIBLE HOME INVASION.

11:26.680 --> 11:29.274
COPY, 1504.
E.M.S. AND BACKUP ARE EN ROUTE.

11:29.320 --> 11:30.719
OH, THANK GOD.

11:30.750 --> 11:31.819
YOU OKAY?

11:31.850 --> 11:33.909
[ Gasping ]
NO. PLEASE HELP ME.

11:33.960 --> 11:36.087
ALL RIGHT.
YOU'RE GONNA BE ALL RIGHT.

11:36.120 --> 11:38.259
[ PANTING ]

11:41.600 --> 11:42.555
SO, YOUR MOM AND DAD WERE GOING
OUT OF TOWN FOR A WEEK?

11:42.600 --> 11:44.067
HE'S NOT MY DAD.

11:44.100 --> 11:46.830
IT'S A MISTAKE THAT MY MOM MADE
FOUR YEARS AGO.

11:46.870 --> 11:49.668
OKAY, POINT IS, THEY WERE
LEAVING YOU HERE ALONE?

11:49.700 --> 11:51.406
I'M 17.

11:51.440 --> 11:53.499
NO SCHOOL TODAY?

11:54.910 --> 11:56.104
COME ON, SETH,

11:56.140 --> 11:59.746
I'M NOT GONNA BUST YOU
FOR SKIPPING ALGEBRA.

12:02.320 --> 12:05.141
I WASN'T EVEN SUPPOSED
TO BE HERE, OKAY?

12:05.190 --> 12:07.784
I-I-I DITCHED
TO GO GET THIS NEW CONSOLE.

12:07.820 --> 12:08.718
STEAM BOX?

12:08.760 --> 12:10.580
YOU GAME?

12:10.630 --> 12:12.427
DO NEWBS GET GANKED?

12:12.460 --> 12:13.996
[ CHUCKLES ]

12:14.030 --> 12:16.453
DIDN'T EVEN GET IT UNWRAPPED.
SOMEBODY STEALS IT.

12:16.500 --> 12:19.219
OKAY, SO YOUR PARENTS
WENT TO THE AIRPORT.

12:19.270 --> 12:20.396
YOU DITCH SCHOOL.

12:20.440 --> 12:22.237
YOU'RE HERE, YOU'RE ALONE.

12:22.270 --> 12:23.931
DID YOU LOCK THE DOORS?

12:23.970 --> 12:24.959
UH, YEAH, YEAH.

12:25.010 --> 12:26.659
I, UH, LOCKED THEM
AI-TER THEY LEI-T.

12:26.710 --> 12:27.904
MY MOM'S SUPER PARANOID.

12:27.940 --> 12:29.737
SO, WHAT HAPPENED?

12:29.780 --> 12:30.906
I DON'T KNOW.

12:30.950 --> 12:34.272
I...I CAME IN,
SOMEBODY JUMPED ME FROM BEHIND,

12:34.320 --> 12:37.312
THEY THREW THAT THING ON
MY HEAD, AND THEY TIED ME UP.

12:37.350 --> 12:41.889
I...I DIDN'T SEE ANYTHING.
IT ALL HAPPENED SO FAST.

12:41.920 --> 12:45.720
AND WHEN MY STEPDAD
CAME IN...

12:45.760 --> 12:49.799
I THOUGHT
THE GUY WAS BACK.

12:49.830 --> 12:53.561
I THOUGHT FOR SURE
I WAS GONNA DIE.

12:54.670 --> 12:55.796
THINK THAT'S IT.

12:55.840 --> 12:57.307
THAT'S A LIST OF EVERYTHING
THAT'S MISSING --

12:57.340 --> 13:00.275
YOU KNOW, LIKE,
THE BEST I CAN TELL.

13:00.310 --> 13:03.507
IT'S, LIKE, iPADS, SILVERWARE,
WHICH IS KIND OF WEIRD.

13:03.550 --> 13:05.871
THANK GOD THEY DIDN'T
GET IN MY STUDIO.

13:05.910 --> 13:07.673
SO YOU'RE A MUSICIAN?
YEAH.

13:07.720 --> 13:08.846
I QUIT MY DAY JOB,

13:08.880 --> 13:11.144
AND NOW I'M --
I'M -- I'M PRODUCING,

13:11.190 --> 13:14.614
YOU KNOW, TRACKS FOR FRIENDS
AND STUFF AND TEACHING GUITAR.

13:14.660 --> 13:16.082
"FOLLOW YOUR BLISS."
RIGHT?

13:16.120 --> 13:17.724
PLEASE DON'T QUOTE
"THE SECRET."

13:17.760 --> 13:18.829
I HAVE A FIREARM.

13:18.860 --> 13:19.929
NO, I'M JUST SAYING THAT,

13:19.960 --> 13:21.393
YOU KNOW, LIKE,
YOU -- WHATEVER.

13:21.430 --> 13:22.454
YOU FIND A JOB YOU LOVE,

13:22.500 --> 13:24.320
AND THEN YOU NEVER WORK A DAY
IN YOUR LIFE.

13:24.370 --> 13:25.598
[ Chuckling ] RIGHT.

13:25.630 --> 13:26.995
WHAT DOES YOUR WIFE DO?

13:27.040 --> 13:28.189
JACQ LYN .

13:28.240 --> 13:30.538
UM, P.R.

13:30.570 --> 13:32.037
SHE HAS HER OWN FIRM.

13:32.070 --> 13:34.903
OH, MY GOD.

13:34.940 --> 13:37.647
I...I HAVE TO CALL HER.
SHE'S AT THE AIRPORT.

13:37.680 --> 13:39.602
MY PHONE'S IN THE CAR.
SHE'S PROBABLY BEEN CALLING.

13:39.650 --> 13:41.845
OKAY.
I'LL GO GRAB IT RIGHT NOW.

13:45.250 --> 13:47.718
IT EAT YOUR MONEY
OR SOMETHING?

13:47.760 --> 13:50.558
NO, NO.
EXISTENTIAL CRISIS.

13:50.590 --> 13:52.785
I WOULD LIKE TO BE
A GRANOLA-BAR GUY,

13:52.830 --> 13:56.197
BUT I KNOW THAT, IN ACT UALITY,
I'M PROBABLY A CANDY-BAR GUY.

13:56.230 --> 13:57.697
AM I SELLING MYSELF SHORT?

13:57.730 --> 13:59.220
I MEAN,
SHOULD I GET ON A PROGRAM?

13:59.270 --> 14:02.694
ALWAYS GOOD WITH THE WORDS.

14:02.740 --> 14:04.059
HOW'S THE CASEWORK COMING?
[ THUD ]

14:04.110 --> 14:07.807
I'D RATHER BE ON THE STREET,
WORKING A SPLIT, IN FEBRUARY.

14:07.840 --> 14:09.478
YEAH, IT WAS EASY, RIGHT?

14:09.510 --> 14:11.375
I MEAN, EVEN WHEN THINGS
WERE BAD,

14:11.410 --> 14:14.470
AT LEAST THEY WERE --
THEY WERE CLEAR.

14:14.520 --> 14:17.683
POLITICS, MAN, HAS NEVER BEEN
MY THING, BUT IT IS NOW.

14:17.720 --> 14:21.588
AND, BROTHER, IT AIN'T --
IT AIN'T ME.

14:21.620 --> 14:23.429
15 USED TO HAVE THIS T.O.
A WHILE BACK,

14:23.460 --> 14:25.428
SECOND BEST IN THE DIVISION --
OLIVER SHAW.

14:25.460 --> 14:26.654
YOU HEARD OF HIM?

14:26.690 --> 14:28.351
YEAH, GOOD-LOOKING GUY,
GREAT WITH THE LADIES.

14:28.400 --> 14:29.526
YEAH, THAT'S HIM.

14:29.560 --> 14:31.425
ANYWAY, HE HAD THIS THING
HE'D SAY TO HIS ROOKIES.

14:31.470 --> 14:32.937
YEAH,
"A ROOKIE ALWAYS PAYS."

14:34.700 --> 14:35.894
"BE THE COP YOU ARE,

14:35.940 --> 14:38.033
NOT THE COP YOU THINK
YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO BE."

14:38.070 --> 14:40.971
[ SIGHS ]

14:41.010 --> 14:42.705
YOU'LL FIGURE IT OUT.

14:44.250 --> 14:47.071
SAM.

14:49.850 --> 14:51.215
ABOUT MCNALLY --

14:51.250 --> 14:53.559
I KNOW YOU WERE
LOOKING OUT FOR HER,

14:53.590 --> 14:56.809
AND MAYBE SHE CAN'T SEE THAT
RIGHT NOW, BUT SHE WILL.

15:04.670 --> 15:06.399
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATION ]

15:06.430 --> 15:08.068
I'M NOT GOING TO APOLOGIZE
FOR INTERRUPTING,

15:08.100 --> 15:10.159
'CAUSE YOU'RE HAPPY TO SEE ME.
YOU JUST DON'T KNOW IT YET.

15:10.210 --> 15:12.770
YOU'RE GIVING ME THE OFFICERS
FOR MY RAID.
HE JUST WRECKED
THE SURPRISE.

15:12.810 --> 15:14.835
THE TEAM'S SUITING UP RIGHT NOW.
WE'RE JUST WAITING ON YOUR WORD.

15:14.880 --> 15:16.336
THANK YOU, STAFF SERGEANT.

15:16.380 --> 15:17.870
Oliver:
YEAH, MAKE IT A CLEAN BUST,

15:17.910 --> 15:20.140
FILL MY CELLS,
WE'LL CALL IT EVEN.

15:20.180 --> 15:22.148
10 MINUTES, WANT THE WHOLE TEAM
IN PARADE FOR A BRIEFING.

15:22.180 --> 15:23.989
YES, SIR.

15:24.020 --> 15:25.647
Steve:
[ Sighing ] OKAY.

15:27.990 --> 15:30.322
GOOD LUCK.
THANKS.

15:34.730 --> 15:37.096
GET ANYTHING
FROM THE NEIGHBORS?

15:37.130 --> 15:38.358
OH, NOTHING MUCH.

15:38.400 --> 15:40.197
THEY PAID TOO MUCH
FOR THEIR HOUSE,

15:40.240 --> 15:41.537
JUST SOLD THEIR SECOND CAR.

15:41.570 --> 15:42.639
WAS THE DAD ANY HELP?

15:42.670 --> 15:45.969
JUST A LONG LIST
OF STOLEN ITEMS.

15:46.010 --> 15:47.602
OKAY, SO THE BAD GUY
HITS THE HOUSE

15:47.640 --> 15:49.198
THE SAME DAY THAT THEY LEAVE
FOR VACATION.

15:49.240 --> 15:50.502
EITHER HE WAS
WATCHING THE PLACE

15:50.550 --> 15:51.847
OR HE KNEW
OF THEIR TRAVEL PLANS.

15:51.880 --> 15:53.370
HE MUST HAVE KNOWN
THE FAMILY, RIGHT?

15:53.420 --> 15:54.978
I MEAN, HOW ELSE
WOULD THEY HAVE KNOWN

15:55.020 --> 15:56.715
THAT EWAN'S DOOR WAS LOCKED
IN THE STUDIO

15:56.750 --> 15:58.308
AND THAT CLOSING IT
WOULD LOCK HIM IN?

15:58.350 --> 16:00.284
[ CELLPHONE BUZZES ]

16:00.320 --> 16:02.254
I GOT TO MAKE A CALL.

16:02.290 --> 16:03.518
OKAY.

16:04.760 --> 16:06.990
WEIRDO.

16:07.030 --> 16:08.429
WHERE'S SETH?
WHERE'S MY SON?

16:08.460 --> 16:10.462
H-HE'S UPSTAIRS. HE'S FINE.
EVERYTHING IS OKAY.

16:10.500 --> 16:11.364
PLEASE.

16:11.400 --> 16:12.719
[ Sighing ] OKAY.

16:12.770 --> 16:14.135
THE OFFICER SAID
WE WERE ROBBED.

16:14.170 --> 16:15.432
DID YOU CATCH
WHOEVER DID IT?

16:15.470 --> 16:17.006
NO, NOT YET.
WE'RE TRYING TO FIGURE OUT

16:17.040 --> 16:18.234
WHO KNEW YOU WERE
GONNA BE OUT OF TOWN.

16:18.270 --> 16:19.601
MY SON WAS ATTACKED,

16:19.640 --> 16:21.278
MY HOME VIOLATED.

16:21.310 --> 16:22.732
THERE ARE POLICE CARS
ON MY LAWN.

16:22.780 --> 16:24.008
THE NEIGHBORS
ARE FREAKING OUT.

16:24.050 --> 16:26.371
JACKIE, JUST -- OKAY?
THEY'RE TRYING TO HELP.

16:26.410 --> 16:27.911
DON'T MAKE THIS
INTO A BIG DEAL.

16:27.950 --> 16:29.349
HE'S FINE.

16:29.380 --> 16:30.381
SWEETHEART, ARE YOU OKAY?

16:30.420 --> 16:31.648
YEAH, I'M FINE, I SWEAR.

16:31.690 --> 16:33.908
OH, I'M SO SORRY
THAT THIS HAPPENED TO YOU.

16:33.960 --> 16:35.552
WHATEVER THEY TOOK,

16:35.590 --> 16:37.478
WE'RE GONNA GET IT BACK,
ALL RIGHT?

16:37.530 --> 16:39.919
[ Sighing ] OKAY.
I'M SO SORRY.

16:39.960 --> 16:41.518
IT'LL BE OKAY.

16:46.870 --> 16:48.861
HOW'D THOSE TWO
END UP MARRIED?

16:48.900 --> 16:51.505
OPPOSITES ATTRACT?
SERIOUSLY.

16:51.540 --> 16:53.701
HE'S LIKE "THE BIG CHILL."
SHE'S STRUNG LIKE A VIOLIN.

16:53.740 --> 16:54.775
HEY, LOOK AT THIS WINDOW.

16:54.810 --> 16:56.232
MOST OF THE GLASS
LANDED OUTSIDE,

16:56.280 --> 16:58.339
WHICH MEANS THIS WINDOW
WAS BROKEN FROM THE INSIDE.

16:58.380 --> 16:59.369
SO, HOW'D THEY GET IN?

16:59.410 --> 17:00.638
I'M THE BAD GUY.

17:00.680 --> 17:01.840
NO FORCED ENTRY.

17:01.880 --> 17:03.984
SO, WHAT,
I PICKED THE LOCK?

17:04.020 --> 17:06.409
SOUNDS LIKE YOU HAD A KEY,
BAD GUY.
MAYBE.

17:06.450 --> 17:08.179
SO I COME IN -- RIGHT? --

17:08.220 --> 17:11.826
I TIE UP SETH, ROB, ROB, ROB,
THEN I BREAK THE WINDOW.

17:11.860 --> 17:13.122
WHY?

17:13.160 --> 17:14.627
IT'S NOISY,
AND SOMEONE MIGHT SEE ME.

17:14.660 --> 17:17.788
BECAUSE YOU DIDN'T WANT ANYONE
TO KNOW HOW YOU GOT IN.

17:17.830 --> 17:19.991
OR MAYBE YOU STAGED
THE WHOLE THING.

17:20.030 --> 17:22.430
OR MAYBE IT WAS
AN INSIDE JOB.

17:25.040 --> 17:26.337
HE DIDN'T SEEM FAZED
BY THE ROBBERY.

17:26.370 --> 17:27.769
20 BUCKS,
HE HIRED SOMEONE TO DO IT.

17:27.810 --> 17:29.300
OH, I'M GONNA TAKE THAT BET.
YOU'RE ON.

17:29.340 --> 17:30.841
SO, WHY WOULD HE GO HOME
IN THE MIDDLE OF IT?

17:30.880 --> 17:31.847
Gail: EXACTLY.

17:31.880 --> 17:34.212
WHO DO YOU LIKE FOR IT,
THE SON?

17:34.250 --> 17:37.139
NO, I MEAN, THAT MEANS HE WOULD
HAVE HAD TO TIE HIMSELF UP.

17:37.190 --> 17:38.885
I THINK MY MONEY
IS ON JACQLYN.

17:38.920 --> 17:41.809
SHE JUST KEPT APOLOGIZING TO
THE KID LIKE IT WAS HER FAULT.

17:41.860 --> 17:42.986
I THINK SHE SET IT UP,

17:43.020 --> 17:44.624
AND SHE DIDN'T EXPECT
THE SON TO BE THERE.

17:44.660 --> 17:46.252
Sam: SO, WHY WOULD SHE LET
HER HUSBAND GO HOME

17:46.290 --> 17:47.052
IN THE MIDDLE OF IT?

17:47.100 --> 17:48.499
EXACTLY.

17:48.530 --> 17:50.862
IT'S TRUE,
THEY BOTH HAVE MEANS.

17:50.900 --> 17:53.391
HIRE SOME GOON, GIVE HIM A KEY
AND OPPORTUNITY.

17:53.440 --> 17:56.034
VACATION'S A GREAT ALIBI,
BUT WHERE'S THE MOTIVE?

17:56.070 --> 17:57.207
RIGHT HERE.

17:57.240 --> 17:59.037
I PULLED THE FAMILY'S
FINANCIALS.

17:59.070 --> 18:01.038
JACQLYN'S P.R. FIRM
IS GOING UNDER.

18:01.080 --> 18:03.640
THEIR HOUSE IS ONE MORTGAGE
PAYMENT AWAY FROM FORECLOSURE,

18:03.680 --> 18:06.342
AND THIS COLLECTION AGENCY IS
ALL OVER THEM FOR UNPAID BILLS.

18:06.380 --> 18:08.917
BUT THEY ALWAYS PAY THEIR HOME
INSURANCE, NO MATTER WHAT.

18:08.950 --> 18:10.042
THAT'S RIGHT.

18:11.290 --> 18:12.689
HA!

18:12.720 --> 18:15.587
YEAH, SO, I CAME IN BECAUSE
THEY SAID THEY NEEDED HELP.

18:15.620 --> 18:17.156
W-WE DO NEED YOUR HELP,
EWAN.

18:17.190 --> 18:18.020
DO YOU?
YES.

18:18.060 --> 18:19.357
SERIOUSLY, MAN.

18:19.390 --> 18:20.891
BECAUSE --
I'LL BE HONEST WITH YOU --

18:20.930 --> 18:22.124
I'M STARTING TO FEEL
A LITTLE TRAPPED HERE --

18:22.160 --> 18:23.991
ALL RIGHT? --
LIKE -- LIKE --

18:24.030 --> 18:25.895
LIKE YOU THINK THAT
MAYBE I DID SOMETHING WRONG.

18:25.930 --> 18:26.692
DO I NEED A LAWYER?

18:26.730 --> 18:27.628
I DON'T KNOW.

18:27.670 --> 18:28.967
DO YOU FEEL LIKE A SUSPECT?

18:29.000 --> 18:30.228
YES.

18:30.270 --> 18:31.237
LOOK, I-I -- PERSONALLY --

18:31.270 --> 18:32.362
I'M GONNA BE HONEST
WITH YOU --

18:32.410 --> 18:33.570
I DIDN'T THINK THAT MYSELF

18:33.610 --> 18:35.976
UNTIL I SAW SOME OF THIS STUFF,
AND THEN --

18:36.010 --> 18:37.147
WHAT IS -- WHAT IS THIS?

18:37.180 --> 18:39.000
BANK RECORDS, LOANS.
SO WHAT? SO WHAT?

18:39.050 --> 18:40.915
WHAT DOES THIS HAVE TO DO
WITH ANYTHING?

18:40.950 --> 18:43.009
WELL, YOU'RE BROKE, EWAN.

18:43.050 --> 18:45.314
BROKE?
YEAH.

18:45.350 --> 18:47.682
[ Laughing ]
ARE YOU KIDDING?

18:47.720 --> 18:49.517
MAN, MY WIFE
HAS HER OWN BUSINESS.

18:49.560 --> 18:51.687
HAVE YOU SEEN OUR HOUSE?
WE'RE NOT BROKE.

18:51.730 --> 18:54.597
Y-YOU'RE ONE PAYMENT AWAY
FROM -- FROM LOSING THAT HOUSE,

18:54.630 --> 18:56.120
AND ACCORDING
TO THIS STATEMENT,

18:56.160 --> 18:58.219
YOUR WIFE'S ABOUT
TO LOSE HER COMPANY.

18:58.270 --> 19:01.364
OKAY.

19:01.400 --> 19:02.628
ALL RIGHT, LISTEN, MAN,

19:02.670 --> 19:06.128
I, UM [Chuckling] I GOT TO
TALK TO JACQLYN ABOUT THIS,

19:06.170 --> 19:07.239
ALL RIGHT?

19:07.280 --> 19:09.339
SHE -- SHE HANDLES
ALL THE MONEY STUFF.

19:09.380 --> 19:11.769
SHE'LL KNOW WHAT...
IS GOING ON.

19:11.810 --> 19:13.414
OKAY.

19:13.450 --> 19:16.317
ALL RIGHT, LOOK, YOU KNOW --
COME HERE.

19:16.350 --> 19:17.886
[ SIGHS ]

19:17.920 --> 19:19.444
BETWEEN YOU AND ME,

19:19.490 --> 19:21.378
PEOPLE AROUND HERE
ARE STARTING TO THINK

19:21.420 --> 19:23.786
THAT MAYBE THIS WAS
AN INSIDE JOB --

19:23.830 --> 19:25.149
INSURANCE FRAUD.

19:25.190 --> 19:27.192
HAPPENS ALL THE TIME.

19:27.230 --> 19:28.390
IT WASN'T.

19:28.430 --> 19:29.351
YOU SURE?

19:29.400 --> 19:30.196
YES, YES.

19:30.230 --> 19:32.369
HOW DO YOU KNOW?

19:32.400 --> 19:33.799
BECAUSE.

19:33.840 --> 19:34.864
WHAT?

19:34.900 --> 19:37.403
BECAUSE I HAD
A STASH OF POT

19:37.440 --> 19:38.839
IN THE STUDIO, OKAY?

19:38.870 --> 19:41.577
AND WHOEVER BROKE IN
TOOK IT.

19:41.610 --> 19:43.840
OKAY, BUT ACCORDING
TO YOUR STATEMENT,

19:43.880 --> 19:45.973
NOTHING WAS STOLEN
FROM THE STUDIO.

19:46.010 --> 19:49.548
YES, BECAUSE IT WAS WEED,
AND YOU GUYS ARE COPS!

19:49.580 --> 19:51.684
ALL RIGHT?
IT WAS IN A STASH CAN.

19:51.720 --> 19:53.950
YOU WOULD HAVE TO KNOW
WHERE IT WAS.

19:53.990 --> 19:56.117
ONLY A COUPLE OF PEOPLE
KNEW THAT.

19:56.160 --> 19:58.628
HELP ME OUT, EWAN.

19:58.660 --> 20:01.220
NAMES WOULD BE
A GREAT START.

20:01.260 --> 20:03.148
A BET'S A BET.

20:10.240 --> 20:12.162
[ CAR DOOR OPENS ]

20:15.840 --> 20:17.944
TRACI, WE CAN'T DO THIS.

20:17.980 --> 20:19.504
MY LAWYER WAS CLEAR,
RIGHT?

20:19.550 --> 20:21.472
NO CONTACT UNTIL AN AGREEMENT
WAS SIGNED.

20:25.950 --> 20:28.054
Traci: YOU AREN'T GOING
TO THERAPY TODAY.

20:28.090 --> 20:30.217
WHAT'S THIS?

20:30.260 --> 20:33.297
SPADINA AND BALDWIN
EVERY WEDNESDAY, 2:00.

20:33.330 --> 20:35.150
IT'S A RESTAURANT.
SO WHAT?

20:35.200 --> 20:36.599
THOSE ARE
SURVEILLANCE PHOTOS.

20:36.630 --> 20:39.098
WE KNOW
ABOUT THE GAMBLING.

20:39.130 --> 20:41.598
[ CHUCKLES LIGHTLY ]
YOU'RE BLACKMAILING ME.

20:41.640 --> 20:43.267
I'M TRYING TO KEEP YOU
OUT OF JAIL.

20:43.310 --> 20:45.266
IF YOU GO THERE TODAY,
YOU'LL BE ARRESTED --

20:45.310 --> 20:47.699
NOT MAYBE, DEFINITELY.

20:47.740 --> 20:50.641
[ SIGHS ]

20:50.680 --> 20:51.999
LOOK, I'M SORRY.

20:52.050 --> 20:53.517
[ SIGHS ]

20:53.550 --> 20:55.108
OKAY, I'M TRYING TO COVER
MY LEGAL FEES.

20:55.150 --> 20:57.175
I-I DIDN'T KNOW HOW ELSE
TO DO IT.
SAVE IT.

20:57.220 --> 21:00.678
JUST -- ALL THAT MATTERS IS THAT
THIS STAYS BETWEEN US, OKAY?

21:03.120 --> 21:04.348
I GET IT.

21:04.390 --> 21:06.358
DEX, I'M SERIOUS.

21:06.390 --> 21:09.689
TRACI, I-I GET IT.
I GET IT.

21:09.730 --> 21:11.766
[ SIGHS ]

21:11.800 --> 21:13.563
I GOT TO GET BACK TO WORK.

21:16.070 --> 21:18.061
[ SIREN WAILS ]

21:22.140 --> 21:24.574
[ SIGHS ]

21:24.610 --> 21:28.046
HELLO? UH, HI, THIS IS OFFICER
EPSTEIN FROM 15 DIVISION.

21:28.080 --> 21:31.743
YEAH. YES, UH, I-I'M SORRY
ABOUT THIS MORNING,

21:31.790 --> 21:35.112
[ CELLPHONE BUZZING ]
BUT I WAS WONDERING
IF IT WOULD BE POSSIBLE

21:35.160 --> 21:36.616
TO, UH, TO RESCHEDULE

21:36.660 --> 21:39.288
MY MEETING
WITH SERGEANT ROLLINS.

21:39.330 --> 21:41.855
YES. NO, I-I-I UNDERSTAND.

21:41.900 --> 21:43.390
HE IS A VERY BUSY MAN,

21:43.430 --> 21:45.762
BUT, I MEAN, COME ON,
IMPOSSIBLE?

21:45.800 --> 21:47.529
FLIGHT USED TO BE
IMPOSSIBLE, RIGHT?

21:47.570 --> 21:48.537
[ CHUCKLES ]

21:48.570 --> 21:49.798
[ BUZZING CONTINUES ]

21:49.840 --> 21:50.966
NO.

21:51.010 --> 21:53.604
I'M JUST SAYING
THAT IT'S ACHIEVABLE.

21:53.640 --> 21:56.677
RESCHEDULING A MEETING
IS ACHIEVABLE.

21:58.710 --> 22:00.302
OKAY.

22:00.350 --> 22:02.113
YEAH, I'LL --
I'LL CALL BACK THEN.

22:02.150 --> 22:03.913
THANK YOU.

22:10.790 --> 22:13.327
[ SIGHS ]
IT'S FINALLY QUIET.

22:13.360 --> 22:15.999
YEAH.
WE'RE ALMOST WRAPPED UP.

22:16.030 --> 22:19.067
YOU, UH, GOT A SUSPECT
OR SOMETHING?

22:19.100 --> 22:20.863
WORKING ON IT.

22:20.900 --> 22:22.538
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

22:22.570 --> 22:26.336
YOU GUYS THINK
MY PARENTS DID IT.

22:26.370 --> 22:28.736
I'M NOT STUPID.

22:28.780 --> 22:31.101
THEY'RE AT THE POLICE STATION,
RIGHT?

22:31.150 --> 22:32.344
DOESN'T MEAN THEY HAD ANYTHING
TO DO WITH IT.

22:32.380 --> 22:34.473
OH.

22:34.520 --> 22:38.980
THEN IT WAS PROBABLY ONE
OF MY STEPDAD'S FRIENDS.

22:39.020 --> 22:42.387
HE SELLS WEED ON THE SIDE.

22:42.420 --> 22:45.821
AND MY MOM HAS NO IDEA.
[ SCOFFS ]

22:45.860 --> 22:48.749
ALL THEY DO IS LIE TO EACH OTHER
AND FIGHT.

22:48.800 --> 22:50.893
EVERYBODY'S FAMILY
HAS STUFF.

22:50.930 --> 22:54.593
YEAH.
YOURS EVER GET YOU BEAT UP?

22:54.640 --> 22:58.201
[ SCOFFS ]
ROBBED THEIR OWN HOUSE?

22:58.240 --> 23:01.368
NO, THEY DIDN'T.

23:01.410 --> 23:03.742
[ SIGHS ]
SETH, I'M SORRY.

23:03.780 --> 23:07.568
[ SIGHS ]
YEAH, ME TOO.

23:07.620 --> 23:09.144
IS THERE SOMEBODY
I CAN CALL --

23:09.180 --> 23:10.886
SOMEBODY THAT CAN
HANG OUT WITH YOU

23:10.920 --> 23:12.319
UNTIL YOUR PARENTS
GET BACK?

23:12.350 --> 23:15.057
NOPE.

23:17.320 --> 23:19.925
THERE'S NOBODY.

23:27.270 --> 23:29.135
SO, YOUR HUSBAND IS GONNA BE
FINISHED SOON.

23:29.170 --> 23:31.707
IN THE MEANTIME, IT'D BE GREAT
IF WE CAN GET YOUR STATEMENT.

23:31.740 --> 23:33.628
OF COURSE. [ SIGHS ]
I HAVE NOTHING TO HIDE.

23:33.680 --> 23:35.932
NOTHING -- NO FINANCIAL CRISIS,
NO LOOMING BANKRUPTCY?

23:37.850 --> 23:39.943
[ SIGHS ]

23:39.980 --> 23:41.447
SORRY.

23:41.480 --> 23:42.777
IT'S OKAY.

23:42.820 --> 23:44.447
IT'S TRUE.

23:44.490 --> 23:46.583
IT'S JUST...DIFFICULT TO HEAR IT
PUT LIKE THAT.

23:46.620 --> 23:48.212
YEAH,
YOU'RE IN FINANCIAL RUIN.

23:48.260 --> 23:50.285
IT'S SUCH A GOOD IDEA
TO TAKE A VACATION.

23:50.320 --> 23:53.756
Jacqun: I BOOKED IT MONTHS AGO.
WE COULDN'T CANCEL IT.

23:53.800 --> 23:55.028
[ SIGHS ]

23:55.060 --> 23:57.119
I THOUGHT MAYBE IT WOULD
HELP...OUR MARRIAGE.

23:57.160 --> 24:00.994
WE'RE...NOT COMMUNICATING
VERY WELL THESE DAYS.

24:01.040 --> 24:04.862
I MUST LOOK LIKE
SUCH AN IDIOT.

24:04.910 --> 24:06.559
NO. HONESTLY.

24:06.610 --> 24:09.602
LOOK, I DON'T KNOW WHAT I WOULD
HAVE DONE IN YOUR POSITION.

24:12.080 --> 24:14.378
WAIT.

24:14.420 --> 24:15.512
DO YOU GUYS THINK

24:15.550 --> 24:16.972
I HAD SOMETHING TO DO
WITH THE ROBBERY?

24:18.720 --> 24:20.608
MY SON WAS ATTACKED.

24:20.660 --> 24:22.719
WE KNOW.

24:22.760 --> 24:25.388
UM, ACTUALLY, WE THINK
THAT THE THIEF KNEW EWAN.

24:25.430 --> 24:27.352
Gail: HIS STASH OF POT WAS TAKEN
FROM HIS STUDIO,

24:27.390 --> 24:30.188
AND HE JUST THINKS THAT
MAYBE ONE OF HIS 420 FRIENDS

24:30.230 --> 24:31.390
MIGHT HAVE HAD SOMETHING
TO DO WITH IT.

24:31.430 --> 24:33.125
[ Chuckling ]
HIS STASH OF WHAT?

24:33.170 --> 24:35.536
HIS POT, HIS WEED,

24:35.570 --> 24:36.935
HIS MARIJUANA.

24:36.970 --> 24:37.868
[ SIGHS ]

24:40.710 --> 24:42.337
WHERE WAS IT?

24:42.380 --> 24:44.302
UNDERNEATH
HIS MIXING BOARD.

24:44.350 --> 24:48.446
BUT EWAN SAID THE THIEF
DIDN'T GO IN THE STUDIO.

24:48.480 --> 24:50.368
YOU SURE THE THIEF
WENT IN THERE?

24:50.420 --> 24:52.513
YES.

24:52.550 --> 24:53.756
WHY?

24:55.690 --> 24:56.714
WE HAVE ANOTHER LEAD.

24:56.760 --> 24:58.785
JACQLYN HID
A MOTION-TRIGGERED NANNY CAM

24:58.830 --> 24:59.979
IN THE HUSBAND'S STUDIO.

25:00.030 --> 25:01.725
IT'S BEEN THERE
A COUPLE WEEKS.

25:01.760 --> 25:03.591
TRUST -- THE FOUNDATION
OF MARRIAGE.

25:03.630 --> 25:05.393
SHE THOUGHT HE WAS CHEATING
ON HER

25:05.430 --> 25:07.898
BECAUSE HE HAD ALL THESE PEOPLE
COMING IN AND OUT OF THE HOUSE,

25:07.940 --> 25:10.090
LIKE COLLEGE KIDS
AND MUSICIANS.

25:10.140 --> 25:11.459
PROBABLY SELLING WEED.

25:11.510 --> 25:13.808
HE STOPPED SHORT OF ADMITTING
IT, BUT A POUND OF KUSH?

25:13.840 --> 25:16.001
THAT'S NOT PERSONAL USE,
EVEN FOR A CHRONIC.

25:16.040 --> 25:18.144
WELL, MAYBE THE CAMERA
CAUGHT WHO STOLE IT.

25:18.180 --> 25:20.375
YEAH. GOOD. OKAY.

25:20.410 --> 25:23.015
PECK, CALL EPSTEIN,
RUN IT DOWN, PLEASE.
OKAY.

25:23.050 --> 25:25.086
I FEEL BAD FOR THAT WOMAN.
YOU KNOW, IT SUCKS.

25:25.120 --> 25:26.747
WHY CAN'T SHE JUST SAY
HOW SHE FEELS

25:26.790 --> 25:28.189
AND TELL HIM
WHAT'S GOING ON?

25:28.220 --> 25:29.585
PATH OF LEAST RESISTANCE.

25:29.620 --> 25:31.952
AVOIDING THINGS IS EASY --
KIND OF LIKE YOU WITH OLIVER.

25:31.990 --> 25:34.094
OR YOU WITH EVERYTHING.

25:37.930 --> 25:40.160
TEAM 2 IS IN POSITION.
MOVING IN.

25:43.270 --> 25:45.465
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

25:47.170 --> 25:49.070
YEAH.

25:49.110 --> 25:51.249
HANDS ON THE BAR!
NOBODY MOVE!

25:51.280 --> 25:53.202
HANDS! HANDS!
LET ME SEE YOUR HANDS!

25:53.250 --> 25:56.071
LOCK IT DOWN!
NOBODY IN OR OUT!

26:14.870 --> 26:17.805
STAND DOWN.

26:17.840 --> 26:20.331
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

26:22.810 --> 26:24.300
THINK THEY'RE TRYING
TO SEND US A MESSAGE?

26:24.350 --> 26:26.978
[ SIGHS ]

26:27.010 --> 26:28.819
OH...

26:28.850 --> 26:30.340
[ STALE DOUGHNUT THUNKS ]

26:30.380 --> 26:32.746
HEY.
HI.

26:32.790 --> 26:35.315
WHAT HAPPENED
WITH THE RAID?

26:35.360 --> 26:37.510
[ SCOFFS ]
NOTHING HAPPENED.

26:37.560 --> 26:39.323
THEY KNEW WE WERE COMING.

26:39.360 --> 26:41.396
THERE'S NOT A SINGLE
SUSPECT -- NOBODY.

26:41.430 --> 26:42.727
NOW MY ASS IS IN THE SLING

26:42.760 --> 26:44.819
UNLESS I CAN FIGURE OUT
WHAT WENT WRONG.

26:44.870 --> 26:45.825
THIS IS [ SCOFFS ]

26:45.870 --> 26:48.930
STEVE...I AM SO SORRY.

26:51.270 --> 26:54.068
OOH.

26:54.110 --> 26:55.372
WHAT'D YOU DO?

26:55.410 --> 26:57.742
I TOLD DEX
TO AVOID THE GAME.

26:57.780 --> 27:00.669
HE SAID HE WASN'T
GONNA TELL ANYBODY.

27:00.720 --> 27:03.314
WHAT, HAVE YOU NOT BEEN
PAYING ATTENTION?

27:03.350 --> 27:05.818
DEX IS A LIAR.

27:05.850 --> 27:08.318
NOW, HE LIES AND HE PLAYS YOU
EVERY TIME.

27:09.760 --> 27:11.489
YOU HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT YOU JUST DID.

27:14.430 --> 27:16.022
HEY, YEAH,
NANNY CAM IS UP.

27:16.060 --> 27:17.493
I'M LOOKING AT OUR GUY NOW.

27:17.530 --> 27:19.589
WHITE, CAUCASIAN MALE,
EARLY 20$.

27:19.630 --> 27:21.734
LOOKS LIKE HE WENT
FOR THE LOCKBOX

27:21.770 --> 27:23.260
BUT WASN'T ABLE TO GET IN.

27:23.300 --> 27:24.767
EWAN SAID HE HAD A HANDGUN
IN THERE.

27:24.810 --> 27:26.766
IT'S COMPLETELY LEGAL.
HE'S GOT ALL THE PAPERWORK.

27:26.810 --> 27:28.698
I WANT YOU TO GET THAT CAMERA
BACK TO THE STATION

27:28.740 --> 27:30.105
AND SEE IF HE CAN GIVE US
AN I.D.

27:30.140 --> 27:32.574
ALL RIGHT, WILL DO.

27:32.610 --> 27:34.248
OH, HEY, MAN,
THERE YOU ARE.

27:34.280 --> 27:36.976
YOU SEEN MY CELLPHONE?

27:37.020 --> 27:39.580
YEAH. GOOD NEWS --
YOUR DEALER TEXTED.

27:39.620 --> 27:42.214
YOU CAN PICK UP YOUR BLOW
Al-TER SHIl-T.

27:42.260 --> 27:44.319
BAD NEWS -- YOU SHOULD REALLY
PUT A PASSWORD ON YOUR PHONE.

27:44.360 --> 27:46.089
OH, AND WE SOLVED THE CASE.

27:46.130 --> 27:48.428
THANKS FOR ALL YOUR HELP
ON THAT.

27:48.460 --> 27:51.190
WHAT? YOU WENT THROUGH
MY TEXT MESSAGES?

27:51.230 --> 27:53.619
YOU LIED ABOUT GETTING CLEAN
AND USED ME FOR COVER.

27:55.400 --> 27:58.403
SETH...

27:58.440 --> 28:01.136
YOU RECOGNIZE
THIS GUY?

28:01.180 --> 28:04.707
UH, NO. NO, IT'S JUST,

28:04.750 --> 28:08.868
IT'S CREEPY [CHUCKLES]
SEEING THE GUY WHO BROKE IN.

28:08.920 --> 28:10.615
ARE YOU SURE YOU'VE NEVER SEEN
HIM BEFORE?

28:10.650 --> 28:11.844
YEAH.

28:11.890 --> 28:14.051
YEAH, I'M SURE.

28:14.090 --> 28:15.557
ALL RIGHT,
WELL, DON'T WORRY.

28:15.590 --> 28:17.387
WE'LL HAVE A POSITIVE I.D.
ON THIS GUY

28:17.420 --> 28:18.626
BEFORE THE END OF THE DAY.

28:24.170 --> 28:28.459
LOOK, DOV,
I ADMIT IT, OKAY?

28:28.500 --> 28:30.297
JUST -- JUST SLOW DOWN
FOR A SECOND.

28:30.340 --> 28:32.103
LOOK, YOU'RE OVERREACTING.

28:32.140 --> 28:34.677
WHY ARE YOU MAKING
SUCH A BIG DEAL OF THIS?

28:34.710 --> 28:36.507
IT'S NOT LIKE
I'M YOUR JUNKIE BROTHER.

28:36.540 --> 28:39.600
YOU SHUT YOUR MOUTH.

28:39.650 --> 28:41.777
I'VE GOT THIS
UNDER CONTROL, MAN.

28:41.820 --> 28:43.117
UNDER CONTROL?
YOU'RE LATE FOR WORK.

28:43.150 --> 28:44.515
WHEN YOU DO SHOW UP, YOU'RE
SO BUSY TRYING TO SCORE,

28:44.550 --> 28:45.312
YOU DON'T DO YOUR JOB.

28:45.350 --> 28:48.251
WELL,
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

28:48.290 --> 28:50.087
ARE YOU --
ARE YOU GONNA RAT ME OUT?

28:50.120 --> 28:52.429
I DON'T KNOW.

28:52.460 --> 28:54.849
[ SCOFFS ]

28:54.900 --> 28:57.653
LOOK, I'M SORRY, MAN.
OKAY?

28:57.700 --> 28:59.622
I MESSED UP,

28:59.670 --> 29:02.696
BUT DON'T DO ANYTHING
STUPID.
[ GUNSHOT ]

29:07.910 --> 29:09.775
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

29:19.090 --> 29:21.354
NO, NO, NO, NO.

29:21.390 --> 29:23.358
HEY, SETH, SETH! HEY!

29:23.390 --> 29:24.789
SETH! COME ON, WAKE UP!

29:24.830 --> 29:26.457
WAKE UP! STAY WITH ME!

29:26.490 --> 29:27.525
HE'S BREATHING.

29:27.560 --> 29:29.118
THIS IS 1504.

29:29.160 --> 29:29.990
WE GOT A TEENAGE MALE

29:30.030 --> 29:31.395
WITH A GUNSHOT WOUND
TO THE HEAD.

29:31.430 --> 29:32.727
WE NEED E.M.S. HERE
RIGHT AWAY.

29:32.770 --> 29:35.591
COME ON, BUDDY, COME ON.
STAY WITH US.

29:35.640 --> 29:37.267
WE'RE GONNA GET YOU OUT OF HERE,
ALL RIGHT?

29:39.970 --> 29:41.005
HEY, HEY, HEY,
STAY STILL, SETH, OKAY?

29:41.040 --> 29:42.769
THE AMBULANCE IS COMING,
BUT YOU CAN'T MOVE.

29:42.810 --> 29:44.277
CAN YOU TELL ME
WHAT HAPPENED?

29:44.310 --> 29:47.768
TIM CROCKETT --
THAT'S THE GUY ON THE VIDEO.

29:47.820 --> 29:49.048
HE'S MY FRIEND.

29:49.080 --> 29:50.570
HE SAID
THAT NO ONE WOULD KNOW.

29:50.620 --> 29:52.042
YOU HELPED HIM
ROB YOUR HOUSE?

29:52.090 --> 29:53.978
WE JUST NEEDED ENOUGH MONEY

29:54.020 --> 29:55.578
SO THAT WE COULD
GET OUT OF HERE.

29:55.620 --> 29:57.827
ALL RIGHT, IT'S OKAY.
IT'S OKAY.

29:57.860 --> 29:59.350
DON'T WORRY ABOUT THAT.

29:59.390 --> 30:00.755
MY STEPDAD CAME BACK,

30:00.790 --> 30:02.052
AND WE PANICKED.

30:02.100 --> 30:03.965
AND TIM SAID THAT [GROANS]

30:04.000 --> 30:06.594
IF WE FAKED IT
THAT WE'D BE OKAY.

30:06.630 --> 30:08.996
OKAY.
BUT THEN YOU GUYS
SAW HIM ON THE VIDEO.

30:09.040 --> 30:11.008
SETH, DON'T WORRY
ABOUT THAT RIGHT NOW.

30:11.040 --> 30:12.200
IT'S GONNA BE ALL RIGHT.

30:12.240 --> 30:13.901
WE'RE GONNA GET YOU
OUT OF HERE.

30:13.940 --> 30:15.168
JUST CALM DOWN.
CHRIS!

30:15.210 --> 30:17.633
I COULDN'T EVEN PULL
THE TRIGGER RIGHT.

30:17.680 --> 30:19.978
I COULDN'T EVEN DO THAT.

30:20.010 --> 30:21.238
HOW BAD IS IT?

30:21.280 --> 30:22.872
I'M NOT SURE.
HE'S LOST A LOT OF BLOOD.

30:22.920 --> 30:24.717
HE'S IN SHOCK.
WHERE'S E.M.S.?

30:24.750 --> 30:27.514
THEY'RE CLOSE.
THERE.

30:27.550 --> 30:29.154
THANK YOU.

30:29.190 --> 30:31.181
ALL RIGHT, I NEED YOU
TO ELEVATE HIS LEGS.

30:31.230 --> 30:32.356
WELL, WE CAN'T MOVE HIM.

30:32.390 --> 30:33.482
WE DON'T HAVE A CHOICE.

30:33.530 --> 30:35.555
WE GOT TO KEEP BLOOD FLOWING
TO HIS BRAIN.

30:42.000 --> 30:43.638
VERY GOOD, SETH.

30:43.670 --> 30:46.207
WE'RE GONNA GET YOU OUT OF HERE
IN NO TIME.

30:49.640 --> 30:51.540
DO -- DO YOU SMELL GAS?

30:55.920 --> 30:58.912
[ GASPS ]
NO. NO, NO, NO.

30:58.950 --> 31:01.316
THE BULLET HOLE.
FROM THE GUNSHOT.

31:04.830 --> 31:06.127
[ GAS HISSING ]
[ SNIFFING ] OH!

31:06.160 --> 31:08.094
THAT'S WHERE THE GAS
IS COMING FROM.

31:09.830 --> 31:11.866
WHERE IS EPSTEIN
WITH THAT CAMERA?

31:11.900 --> 31:12.992
I DON'T KNOW.

31:13.030 --> 31:15.635
MAYBE THEY GOT CAUGHT UP
CLOSING DOWN THE SCENE.

31:15.670 --> 31:17.558
LAB GUYS LOVE
TO PAD THEIR HOURS.

31:17.600 --> 31:20.137
EVERYONE ELSE IS GONE
EXCEPT FOR DOV AND CHRIS.

31:20.170 --> 31:21.535
HMM.

31:21.580 --> 31:22.933
I'LL CALL DISPATCH, SEE IF
WE CAN GET THEM ON THE RADIO.

31:22.980 --> 31:24.538
YEAH, GOOD.

31:26.710 --> 31:29.611
OKAY, WE --
WE GOT TO GET OUT OF HERE.

31:29.650 --> 31:30.981
WE'RE GONNA HAVE TO RISK
MOVING HIM.

31:41.900 --> 31:43.049
WE'RE TRAPPED.

31:43.100 --> 31:44.727
WHAT?

31:44.770 --> 31:46.123
I'M SERIOUS.
I-I-IT'S LOCKED.

31:46.170 --> 31:48.536
THE DOOR MUST HAVE CLOSED
BEHIND ME.

31:50.070 --> 31:50.866
WAIT.
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

31:50.900 --> 31:53.232
RADIOING FOR HELP.

31:53.270 --> 31:54.430
WELL, WHAT ABOUT THE GAS?

31:54.480 --> 31:55.833
THE ELECTRICITY FROM THE RADIO
COULD SET IT OFF.

31:55.880 --> 31:57.507
IF WE DON'T GET HELP,
WE'RE DEAD.

32:03.720 --> 32:04.914
[ CLICK, STATIC ]

32:07.150 --> 32:09.254
1504 TO RADIO. 10-33.

32:09.290 --> 32:11.258
I REPEAT, 10-33.

32:11.290 --> 32:13.781
BE ADVISED, THERE IS A GAS LEAK
ON THE PREMISES.

32:13.830 --> 32:15.798
WE'RE TRAPPED IN A ROOM
ON THE FIRST FLOOR

32:15.830 --> 32:17.650
ON THE SOUTHEAST CORNER.

32:17.700 --> 32:20.589
I REPEAT --
WE ARE TRAPPED.

32:20.630 --> 32:23.838
[ SIREN WAILS ]

32:23.870 --> 32:27.704
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

32:27.740 --> 32:29.776
THERE'S A GAS LEAK.

32:29.810 --> 32:31.949
THEY'RE WORKING ON SHUTTING
THE GAS AND THE POWER DOWN,

32:31.980 --> 32:33.277
BUT WE CAN'T GO IN
UNTIL THEN.

32:33.310 --> 32:34.777
WELL,
WE CAN'T JUST STAND HERE.

32:34.820 --> 32:36.549
IF THAT WHOLE HOUSE
IS FILLED WITH GAS,

32:36.580 --> 32:37.717
ONE LITTLE SPARK COULD...

32:40.120 --> 32:43.157
HE'S BLEEDING OUT.
WE GOT TO GET OUT OF HERE NOW.

32:50.100 --> 32:52.466
[ Grunting ] I SHOULD HAVE
NEVER SAID THAT.

32:52.500 --> 32:53.865
YOU SHOULDN'T HAVE DONE
A LOT OF THINGS.

32:53.900 --> 32:55.891
I JUST FEEL LIKE...

32:55.940 --> 32:57.589
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]
I HAD THIS FEELING...

32:57.640 --> 33:00.336
EVERYTHING HAS BEEN
GRINDING ME DOWN.

33:00.370 --> 33:04.306
I JUST, LIKE, WOKE UP --
I WOKE UP ONE DAY, AND IT...

33:04.350 --> 33:05.703
[ CYMBAL CLANGS ]

33:05.750 --> 33:06.808
IT WAS GRAY.

33:08.720 --> 33:10.847
CHRIS?

33:10.880 --> 33:12.780
CHRIS!

33:12.820 --> 33:14.117
CHRIS, NO, NO, NO.

33:14.160 --> 33:16.253
NO, CHRIS.

33:16.290 --> 33:17.257
COME ON.

33:17.290 --> 33:19.485
NO, CHRIS.
WAKE UP, MAN.

33:19.530 --> 33:22.226
WAKE UP. COME ON.
CHRIS!

33:23.860 --> 33:25.088
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

33:27.070 --> 33:28.389
[ CLATTER ]

33:39.180 --> 33:40.249
HEY.

33:40.280 --> 33:42.419
COME ON. GET UP.

33:42.450 --> 33:43.519
WHAT HAPPENED?

33:43.550 --> 33:45.415
GET UP.
GET UP!

33:45.450 --> 33:46.485
WE GOT TO --
[ GROANS ]

33:46.520 --> 33:48.010
WE GOT TO GET SETH
OUT OF HERE.

33:53.030 --> 33:54.497
OKAY.

33:54.530 --> 33:56.259
LET'S GO.

33:56.300 --> 33:57.653
OKAY. OKAY.

33:57.700 --> 33:59.099
OKAY, CAREFUL.

33:59.130 --> 34:00.825
READY?

34:00.870 --> 34:03.430
1...2...3.

34:03.470 --> 34:06.303
OKAY, NICE AND EASY.

34:07.970 --> 34:09.801
YEAH, YEAH. GREAT.
THAN KS.

34:09.840 --> 34:10.807
OKAY, POWER'S OFF.
LET'S GET IN THERE.

34:10.840 --> 34:11.772
SAM.

34:11.810 --> 34:14.813
THEY'RE COMING OUT!
LET'S GO!

34:24.230 --> 34:26.983
ALL RIGHT, 1...2.

34:34.670 --> 34:36.490
[ SIREN WAILS ]

34:39.970 --> 34:41.506
YOU OKAY?

34:41.540 --> 34:42.837
YEAH, I THINK SO.

34:42.880 --> 34:45.769
MEDIC SAID THE KID
SHOULD PULL THROUGH.

34:45.810 --> 34:47.038
SOUNDS LIKE DIAZ
OWES YOU A BEER.

34:51.420 --> 34:53.479
UH, YOU KNOW,
I-I-I-I GOT TO SIT DOWN.

34:53.520 --> 34:55.215
YOU MIND IF I SIT
IN YOUR CAR?

34:55.260 --> 34:57.080
OF COURSE.

35:06.100 --> 35:07.362
BUST WAS A BUST.

35:07.400 --> 35:08.537
YEAH, I HEARD.

35:08.570 --> 35:11.459
IT WAS NICE, THOUGH.
THEY LEI-T TREATS.

35:11.510 --> 35:13.808
A LOT OF CRIMINALS
FORGET THAT PERSONAL TOUCH.

35:13.840 --> 35:16.570
REALLY MAKES A DIFFERENCE.

35:16.610 --> 35:17.634
ALTHOUGH
THE ONLY PROBLEM IS

35:17.680 --> 35:19.341
NOW I KIND OF
WANT TO EAT ONE.

35:19.380 --> 35:22.679
OR WOULD THAT BE PERPETUATING
A NEGATIVE STEREOTYPE?

35:24.950 --> 35:28.579
ACCEPTING A BRIBE?
DESTROYING EVIDENCE?

35:28.620 --> 35:30.053
NOTHING?
YOU'RE NOT --

35:30.090 --> 35:31.887
YOU'RE NOT LISTENING TO ME
AT ALL, ARE YOU?
SORRY.

35:31.930 --> 35:34.694
JUST THESE PHOTOS ON
THE BOARD -- THE DATE STAMPS.

35:34.730 --> 35:36.550
WHEN DID STEVE START
SURVEILLANCE ON THESE GUYS?

35:36.600 --> 35:38.329
THAT WAS A MONTH AGO.

35:38.370 --> 35:39.792
WHY?

35:39.830 --> 35:41.832
THESE PHOTOS
ARE FROM TWO MONTHS AGO.

35:41.870 --> 35:43.895
THEN THOSE AREN'T
FROM THIS CASE.

35:43.940 --> 35:48.400
RIGHT.
THEY MUST BE MISFILED.

35:48.440 --> 35:51.273
TAKE IT UP
WITH DETECTIVE PECK.

35:53.210 --> 35:55.872
YOU SAID THIS HAD NOTHING
TO DO WITH ME.

35:55.920 --> 35:57.376
THIS WAS ALL ABOUT ME.

35:57.420 --> 35:58.910
NO, NOW IS NOT THE TIME.

35:58.950 --> 36:00.941
THESE ARE NOT
FROM THE CASE.

36:00.990 --> 36:02.719
YOU WERE FOLLOWING DEX.
WHY?

36:02.760 --> 36:04.455
I'M SERIOUS, YOU DON'T WANT TO
HAVE THIS CONVERSATION HERE.

36:04.490 --> 36:05.889
ANSWER THE QUESTION.

36:05.930 --> 36:07.682
WOW. OKAY.

36:07.730 --> 36:10.119
IN CASE YOU MISSED
THAT POLICE LESSON IN COLLEGE,

36:10.160 --> 36:12.390
WHAT YOU DID TODAY
WAS GROUNDS FOR DISMISSAL.

36:12.430 --> 36:15.137
OH, WHAT, YOU TAILING MY EX
WITH ZERO PROBABLE CAUSE?

36:15.170 --> 36:17.058
WHAT IS THAT,
SOLID DETECTIVE WORK?

36:17.100 --> 36:18.237
NO, I HAD HIM FOLLOWED

36:18.270 --> 36:20.602
BECAUSE I THOUGHT HE WAS
A DEADBEAT AND A PROBLEM.

36:20.640 --> 36:22.779
YOU KNOW WHAT?
I WAS RIGHT ABOUT BOTH, OKAY?

36:22.810 --> 36:24.277
I WAS JUST LOOKING OUT
FOR YOU.

36:24.310 --> 36:25.174
IT WAS WRONG.

36:25.210 --> 36:26.768
[ SCOFFS ] GREAT.

36:26.810 --> 36:29.870
PECK, WHAT HAPPENED?

36:29.920 --> 36:31.547
I'M JUST PIECING
THAT TOGETHER MYSELF.

36:31.590 --> 36:35.458
YOU TOLD ME THAT THIS BUST WAS
GONNA BE A WIN FOR BOTH OF US.

36:35.490 --> 36:36.957
YEAH.

36:36.990 --> 36:38.821
NOW I HAVE TO EXPLAIN TO THE
INSPECTOR WHY I GAVE YOU A TEAM

36:38.860 --> 36:41.454
OF UNIFORMS TO KICK IN A DOOR
WITH NOTHING ON THE OTHER SIDE.

36:41.500 --> 36:44.094
OLIVER,
THIS WASN'T STEVE'S FAULT.

36:44.130 --> 36:47.122
NO, OF COURSE IT WAS.
MY INTEL WAS WRONG.

36:47.170 --> 36:51.095
THOUGHT I KNEW WHAT I WAS
GETTING INTO, BUT I WAS WRONG.

36:51.140 --> 36:54.268
MY APOLOGIES FOR WASTING
YOUR TIME, STAFF SERGEANT.

36:59.550 --> 37:00.642
[ BRIEFCASE SLAMS SHUT ]

37:11.290 --> 37:13.121
HEY, MAN, ARE WE GOOD?

37:14.430 --> 37:18.890
LOOK...DOV...
I'M GONNA GET IT TOGETHER.

37:18.930 --> 37:20.591
ALL RIGHT?

37:20.630 --> 37:22.962
I MEAN, RELAPSES ARE JUST PART
OF THE RECOVERY PROCESS.

37:23.000 --> 37:24.558
LOOK, I'M GOING
TO ANOTHER MEETING

37:24.610 --> 37:26.009
AS SOON AS
I FINISH WORK HERE.

37:26.040 --> 37:27.962
I'M NOT KEEPING YOUR SECRET
FOR YOU ANYMORE.

37:28.010 --> 37:29.477
I'M GOING TO TALK
TO OLIVER.

37:29.510 --> 37:31.546
WAIT! LOOK,
I'M GONNA LOSE MY JOB.

37:31.580 --> 37:33.707
I KNOW HOW THIS WORKS. I HAD
A JUNKIE BROTHER. REMEMBER?

37:33.750 --> 37:35.547
THE MORE I HELP YOU
KEEP YOUR SECRET,

37:35.580 --> 37:37.070
THE LONGER YOU AVOID
DEALING WITH IT.

37:39.290 --> 37:40.985
AND I'LL FIND YOU
HANGING FROM THE CEILING

37:41.020 --> 37:41.987
OR DEAD FROM AN OVERDOSE.

37:42.020 --> 37:43.612
I LOSE YOU EITHER WAY.

37:43.660 --> 37:45.855
JUST -- LOOK.

37:52.370 --> 37:54.930
I'LL TALK TO HIM.

37:54.970 --> 37:56.460
OKAY?

37:56.500 --> 37:58.934
I'LL TELL HIM THE TRUTH.

38:03.110 --> 38:05.943
I MEAN, YOU KNOW HE'S GONNA FIRE
ME RIGHT ON THE SPOT, RIGHT?

38:05.980 --> 38:07.470
MAYBE.
MAYBE HE'LL HELP YOU.

38:07.510 --> 38:10.570
OH.

38:10.620 --> 38:12.588
SO MUCH
FOR BACKING ME UP.

38:15.760 --> 38:18.422
DOV?

38:18.460 --> 38:20.678
HEY, I'VE BEEN TRYING
TO CALL YOU.

38:20.730 --> 38:22.220
SO, HOW ARE YOU FEELING?

38:22.260 --> 38:24.228
FINE.

38:24.260 --> 38:26.194
WHY DON'T WE GO
GET A BITE TO EAT?

38:26.230 --> 38:28.369
I MEAN, THE TWO OF US
HAVEN'T HUNG OUT

38:28.400 --> 38:29.731
IN, LIKE, FOREVER, RIGHT?

38:29.770 --> 38:31.658
YEAH, I THINK I'D RATHER
JUST BE ALONE TONIGHT,

38:31.710 --> 38:32.529
IF THAT'S ALL RIGHT.

38:32.570 --> 38:35.277
[ Sighing ] OKAY.

38:37.440 --> 38:39.078
DOV, I JUST WANT
TO TALK TO YOU.

38:41.150 --> 38:44.210
LOOK...NOT TONIGHT.

38:44.250 --> 38:48.380
SORRY, CHLOE,
JUST [SIGHS] NOT TONIGHT.

38:48.420 --> 38:50.957
DOV.

38:50.990 --> 38:52.855
[ SIGHS ]

38:52.890 --> 38:54.391
WRONG AGAIN.

38:54.430 --> 38:58.298
BUT, HEY, AT LEAST
I'M CONSISTENT.

38:58.330 --> 38:59.763
KEEP IT.

38:59.800 --> 39:02.030
FINE.
YOU KNOW WHAT?

39:02.070 --> 39:03.867
NICE ANDY WOULD INSIST
THAT YOU TAKE IT BACK,

39:03.900 --> 39:08.109
BUT MEAN ANDY...
IS GONNA POCKET IT, SUCKA.

39:08.140 --> 39:10.404
[ CHUCKLES ]

39:10.440 --> 39:11.668
WHAT?

39:12.910 --> 39:14.514
DON'T GIVE ME THAT LOOK,
OKAY?

39:14.550 --> 39:16.279
YOU'VE BEEN DIGGING MEAN ANDY
ALL DAY.

39:16.320 --> 39:17.275
I CAN ADMIT IT.

39:17.320 --> 39:18.787
PART OF ME
FOUND IT KIND OF COZY

39:18.820 --> 39:19.787
SEEING YOU BE A BITCH.

39:19.820 --> 39:21.913
IT SORT OF --
WELL, IT FED ME --

39:21.960 --> 39:24.781
FED A BITTER, PETTY THING
I'VE GOT GOING ON.

39:24.830 --> 39:25.888
GLAD TO BE OF SERVICE.

39:25.930 --> 39:27.488
THE THING IS,
YOU'RE NOT VERY GOOD AT IT.

39:27.530 --> 39:30.522
BEING MEAN ANDY
IS LIKE BEING GAIL PECK,

39:30.560 --> 39:34.769
AND WHILE THERE ARE JUST A SLEW
OF ADVANTAGES TO BEING ME,

39:34.800 --> 39:37.462
I SUGGEST, WHATEVER YOU GOT
GOING ON, TO JUST GET OVER IT.

39:37.500 --> 39:38.762
OLIVER LOVES YOU.

39:38.810 --> 39:40.835
[ LOCKER DOOR CLOSES ]

39:40.870 --> 39:43.338
HE LOVES ALL OF US.

39:43.380 --> 39:50.809
* AND SO THEY SAY, LORD,
FOR EVERYTHING A REASON *

39:50.850 --> 39:58.757
* FOR EVERY ENDING,
A NEW BEGINNING *

39:58.790 --> 40:01.725
* OH, SO THEY SAY, BABY...

40:01.760 --> 40:03.318
HEY.
HEY.

40:03.360 --> 40:05.089
GOOD TO GO?

40:05.130 --> 40:08.167
* ...EVERYTHING A REASON

40:08.200 --> 40:11.192
I'LL MEET YOU AT THE TRUCK.

40:11.240 --> 40:13.003
TAKE YOUR TIME.

40:13.040 --> 40:15.338
* ...FOR EVERYTHING A REASON

40:15.380 --> 40:23.549
* AND THOSE WHO LOVED BEFORE
WILL BE BROUGHT BACK TOGETHER *

40:23.580 --> 40:30.315
* YEAH, THOSE WHO LOVED BEFORE
WILL BE BROUGHT BACK TOGETHER *

40:30.360 --> 40:38.665
* AND SO THEY SAY, BABY,
FOR EVERYTHING A REASON *

40:38.700 --> 40:40.190
YOU OKAY?

40:40.230 --> 40:43.563
NO. NO.
I'M SUPER CRAPPY.

40:43.600 --> 40:45.636
IT'S LIKE I DID SOMETHING
TO WEDNESDAY,

40:45.670 --> 40:47.331
AND IT'S EXACTING
ITS REVENGE.

40:47.370 --> 40:51.773
I DON'T KNOW WHAT TO DO...
ABOUT US.

40:51.810 --> 40:53.801
YOU KNOW, THE SITUATION --
I JUST --

40:53.850 --> 40:55.545
I REALLY WANT IT
TO BE OVER --

40:55.580 --> 40:56.774
OR OVER IT.

40:56.820 --> 40:58.811
AND YOU'RE NOT?
NO, I'M NOT.

40:58.850 --> 41:00.545
NOT AT ALL.

41:00.590 --> 41:04.686
I SAID TO MYSELF, "SELF --"
THAT'S WHAT I CALL MYSELF.

41:04.730 --> 41:06.220
I SAID,
"SELF, LET'S PRETEND.

41:06.260 --> 41:10.128
"OKAY, PUT A SMILE ON YOUR FACE
AND ACT AS IF YOU'RE HAPPY,

41:10.160 --> 41:13.197
AND MAYBE YOU'LL START
TO FEEL HOW YOU ACT."

41:13.230 --> 41:16.996
IT'S -- IT'S NOT MY IDEA.
I GOT IT ONLINE.

41:17.040 --> 41:19.429
IT'S CALLED "ACT AS IF."

41:19.470 --> 41:22.473
AND IT'S...STUPID, OKAY?

41:22.510 --> 41:23.807
BUT I DON'T KNOW
WHAT ELSE TO DO.

41:23.840 --> 41:25.341
I MEAN, ARE YOU ACTUALLY OKAY
WITH THIS?

41:25.380 --> 41:27.678
NO. NO.

41:27.710 --> 41:29.712
AND I DON'T THINK
THAT'S STUPID.

41:29.750 --> 41:33.083
I [SIGHS]

41:33.120 --> 41:34.781
I...

41:34.820 --> 41:36.708
* MY HOUSE IS HAUNTED...

41:36.760 --> 41:38.523
[ SIGHS ]

41:38.560 --> 41:40.221
* ...BY ROTTEN DESIRE

41:40.260 --> 41:41.591
I'M ON YOUR SIDE, ANDY.

41:41.630 --> 41:43.393
I ALWAYS HAVE BEEN.

41:43.430 --> 41:45.022
I ALWAYS WILL BE.

41:45.070 --> 41:50.929
* AND ON MY SKIN LEI-T THE SCENT
OF INDIGNATION *

41:50.970 --> 41:53.837
* AND SO THEY SAY, BABY...
OKAY.

41:53.870 --> 41:59.445
* FOR EVERYTHING A REASON
HEY, ANDY.

41:59.480 --> 42:00.902
[ SIGHS ]

42:00.950 --> 42:03.111
THIS HAS BEEN THE BEST PART
OF MY DAY, BY A LONG SHOT.

42:03.150 --> 42:05.289
I JUST -- IF YOU CAN
BELIEVE THAT. THANK YOU.

42:05.320 --> 42:08.187
YEAH, I CAN BELIEVE IT.
I MEAN, I'M AMAZING.

42:08.220 --> 42:09.653
[ CHUCKLES ]

42:09.690 --> 42:11.578
* AND SO THEY SAY, BABY...

42:11.630 --> 42:14.326
"ACT AS IF."

42:17.200 --> 42:19.964
* COME BACK TO ME
